headlines.description: No. 1 Clemson emphatically claimed its spot in the College Football Playoff with a 38-3 victory over No. 7 Miami in the Atlantic Coast Conference championship game Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bryant, No. 1 Clemson pound No. 7 Miami 38-3 for ACC crown

video.headline: Clemson earns ACC title with win over Miami

headlines.description: The Georgia Bulldogs get their revenge on Auburn, dismantling the Tigers 28-7 to win their first SEC title since 2005 -- and likely secure a spot in the college football playoff.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia avenged, silences Auburn to win SEC

events.name: TCU Horned Frogs at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Baker Mayfield threw four touchdowns and No. 2 Oklahoma staked claim to a playoff spot with a 41-17 win over No. 10 TCU in the return of the Big 12 championship game Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 2 Oklahoma stakes playoff spot, 41-17 over No. 10 TCU

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: J.T. Barrett threw two touchdown passes, ran for another and had a crucial fourth-down conversion late in the game to give the Buckeyes a 27-21 victory over previously unbeaten No. 3 Wisconsin in Saturday's Big Ten championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrett leads No. 8 Ohio State past No. 3 Wisconsin 27-21

headlines.description: Central Florida for the second straight week prevailed in a shootout on its home field.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 12 UCF captures AAC title over No. 16 Memphis in 2 OTs

video.headline: Neal's INT seals a UCF win

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Neal's INT seals a UCF win) 2017/12/2

events.name: Fresno State Bulldogs at Boise State Broncos

headlines.description: Brett Rypien threw for 246 yards and led a fourth-quarter comeback to help Boise State beat No. 25 Fresno State 17-14 on Saturday night in the Mountain West championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boise State rallies to beat No. 25 Fresno State 17-14

video.headline: Boise State takes Mountain West honors

headlines.description: Logan Woodside threw four touchdown passes and Terry Swanson rushed for 180 yards and two scores as Toledo defeated Akron 45-28 in the Mid-American Conference championship game Saturday at Ford Field.
headlines.shortLinkText: Woodside throws 4 TDs in Toledo's 45-28 MAC title game win

video.headline: Johnson makes sweet one-handed TD snag for Toledo

events.name: North Texas Mean Green at Florida Atlantic Owls

headlines.description: Lane Kiffin's first season at Florida Atlantic brought the school's first Conference USA championship, as the Owls defeated North Texas 41-17 for the league title on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lane's a champ: FAU tops North Texas for C-USA title, 41-17

video.headline: FAU coasts by North Texas to claim C-USA title

events.name: UMass Minutemen at Florida Intl Golden Panthers

headlines.description: Alex McGough passed for 296 yards and three touchdowns and added 108 rushing yards and another score, and FIU beat UMass 63-45 on Saturday to tie a program record for most wins in a season.
headlines.shortLinkText: FIU sets records in 63-45 win over UMass

events.name: Louisiana Monroe Warhawks at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Cam Akers and Jacques Patrick each ran for two touchdowns as Florida State won its third straight game to secure a bowl bid with a 42-10 win over Louisiana Monroe on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Florida State keeps bowl streak alive with rout

video.headline: FSU secures bowl eligibility with win over Louisiana Monroe

events.name: Georgia Southern Eagles at Coastal Carolina Chanticleers

headlines.description: Kilton Anderson threw for two touchdowns to Malcolm Williams, Osharmar Abercrombie ran for two touchdowns and Coastal Carolina defeated Georgia Southern 28-17 on Saturday in the season finale for both teams.

video.headline: Coastal Carolina's Anderson airs out 67-yard TD

events.name: Idaho Vandals at Georgia State Panthers

headlines.description: Colton Richardson threw for 228 yards and a score and Alfonso Onunwor had four catches for 100 yards and a touchdown and Idaho, playing in its final FBS game, beat Georgia State 24-10 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Idaho exits FBS play with 24-10 win over Georgia St.

video.headline: Saunders plunges in for Idaho TD

events.name: Stony Brook Seawolves at James Madison Dukes

notes.headline: NCAA DIVISION I FOOTBALL CHAMPIONSHIP - SECOND ROUND

headlines.description: James Madison's goal is to repeat as the FCS national champion, but the Dukes began their playoff run by asserting dominance in CAA Football on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: James Madison picks apart Stony Brook for FCS playoff win

video.headline: Sharp reaches for James Madison TD

events.name: Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns at Appalachian State Mountaineers

headlines.description: Taylor Lamb passed for four touchdowns and ran for another to help Appalachian State wrap up a share of the Sun Belt Conference title with a 63-14 win over Louisiana-Lafayette on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Appalachian State cruises to share of Sun Belt title

video.headline: Appalachian State's Hennigan makes 4th TD grab of the game

events.name: South Alabama Jaguars at New Mexico State Aggies

headlines.description: Tyler Rogers passed for 451 yards and led a drive that brought New Mexico State back into the lead in the final minute in a 22-17 win over South Alabama on Saturday that made the Aggies eligible for their first bowl since 1960.
headlines.shortLinkText: New Mexico State ends 57-year bowl drought

events.name: Troy Trojans at Arkansas State Red Wolves

headlines.description: Brandon Silvers threw two touchdown passes, including the game-winner with 17 seconds left, and Troy beat Arkansas State 32-25 in a wild finish on Saturday night for a share of the Sun Belt Conference title.
headlines.shortLinkText: Troy scores with 17 seconds left, beats Arkansas State 32-25
